JD 4:

Essential Functions

-Lead category-level analysis to identify performance trends, operational inefficiencies, and strategic opportunities.
-Support and may lead end-to-end category performance analysis, identifying opportunities for cost reduction, service improvement, and operational efficiency.
-Leads strategic sourcing and RFx events for medium to large and complex projects. Subject matter expert in strategic sourcing for assigned categories. Supports other Category Specialists and Manager with sourcing activities.
-Strong communication skills with the ability to utilize data and insights to form a story that drives value. Ability to communication with senior leaders across the business.
-Participates in and supports performance and process improvement initiatives defined by the category plan including strategic sourcing and other initiatives in support of supply chain excellence.
-Ability to lead and develop medium level negotiation plans and understands negotiation levers to achieve the best outcomes. Participates in more complex negotiations as directed by Category Manager.
-Collaborate with key stakeholders to align category strategies with broader supply chain objectives.
-Drive root cause analysis and resolution of supply chain disruptions, implementing sustainable corrective actions.
-Drive and support strategic initiatives such as network optimization, inventory modeling, and scenario planning.
-Review and analyze raw data to build cost models (using spreadsheets, organizing data, creating graphs) and identify savings / avoidance opportunities
-Analyze data and create reports and presentations regarding key business measures such as supplier performance, spend analytics and market trends.
-Review, analyze, and approve purchase requests with established suppliers
-Understand savings and operational targets and develop and execute on plans to deliver on targets
-Encompasses duties of Category Analyst
-Other duties as assigned

