Reporting: Preparing reports and presentations on procurement activities, including spend analysis, supplier performance, and cost savings. 
Research/Inquiries: Staying informed about market trends and supplier developments to inform procurement decisions, and performing detective work on miscellaneous procurement matters to solve problems 
Compliance: Ensuring compliance with internal procurement policies 
Project Management: Supporting the extended global procurement team in overall management systems (meetings and administration, storing files in repositories, key performance indicators, supplier performance management, RFP/RFQ/RFI, Service tickets, ad hoc purchases, preparing charts, leverage AI to innovate)

-Strategic Procurement Category & Vendor Relationship Management: Supporting:
Development, execution and implementation of Strategic projects/initiatives
Propose and define categories strategies – identify opportunities working close to the sites/entities
Partner and build positive relationships, representing Procurement across cross-functional business teams. 
Manage relationships with suppliers / introduce new providers / consolidate spend / create global-regional providers
Establish credibility and engage and influence others to ensure the most effective and efficient solutions are implemented

