JD 39:

What success looks like in this role:

• Manages IT Category suppliers (software, hardware, telecom).
• Negotiates agreements, amendments and other supplier contracts with new and existing suppliers.
• Responsible to liaise with one or more business units or corporate functions to ensure ongoing visibility to requirements.
• Responsible for category management of one or more subcategories.
• Runs requests for information or proposal to assist in the selection of new suppliers and/or to reduce run-rate spend.
• Analyzes budget, cost and spend across the company, identifying trends and methods to reduce costs and improve quality.
• Assists procurement leadership with design and implementation of appropriate internal controls, accounting and reporting procedures.
• Leads or serves as key team member on projects with strategic, financial and global impact.
• Advises leadership on potential procurement issues associated with business expansion, contraction, etc.
• Leads continuous business process improvement by recommending process enhancement and expanding the use of technologies, tools and processes.

