JD 51:

Responsibilities

Category Strategy Development – Design and implement procurement strategies for defined IT and technology sub-categories, ensuring alignment with business needs and market trends.
Supplier Management – Build and maintain relationships with key technology vendors (including Tier 1/Tier 2), negotiate contracts, manage performance, and ensure compliance with agreed service levels.
Cost & Cash Optimization – Identify and deliver cost savings and cash flow improvements through effective negotiations, demand management, and process efficiencies.
Project & Pipeline Management – Build a robust pipeline of sourcing and savings initiatives, monitor progress, and ensure timely delivery against targets.
Budgeting & Forecasting – Provide input into procurement budgets, track actual spend against forecasts, and support financial planning processes.
Sustainability & Compliance – Ensure responsible procurement practices, embedding ESG and CSR objectives into sourcing strategies.
Stakeholder Engagement – Partner with cross-functional teams (IT, Finance, Legal, Operations, HR, etc.) to deliver business value and support strategic objectives.
Leadership & Collaboration – Lead cross-functional project teams, mentor junior colleagues, and contribute to procurement excellence initiatives.

